@page
@model RulesModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Community Guidelines";
}

<div class="rules-container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p><strong>Last Updatd:</strong> June 2026</p>

    <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
    <p>
        VidCore is built on the principles of creative freedom, open expression,
        and respect for other people.
    </p>

    <p>
        We believe users should have the freedom to create, discuss, and share ideas
        as long as they do not harm others or the platform itself.
    </p>

    <h2>Freedom of Content</h2>
    <p>The following content is generally allowed:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Creative works and artistic expression</li>
        <li>Educational content</li>
        <li>Entertainment content</li>
        <li>Discussions and opinions</li>
        <li>Profanity and strong language</li>
        <li>Historical, political, and ideological discussions</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Prohibited Content</h2>

    <h3>Violence and Harm</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Real-world gore and graphic violence</li>
        <li>Content promoting self-harm</li>
        <li>Content encouraging violence against individuals or groups</li>
        <li>Instructions for committing violent crimes</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Terrorism and Extremism</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Terrorist propaganda</li>
        <li>Recruitment for terrorist organizations</li>
        <li>Promotion of terrorism</li>
        <li>Support for terrorist acts</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Hate and Harassment</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Harassment and targeted abuse</li>
        <li>Threats against other users</li>
        <li>Content intended to incite hatred or violence</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Illegal Activity</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Fraud and scams</li>
        <li>Malware and malicious software distribution</li>
        <li>Illegal services</li>
        <li>Content that violates applicable laws</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Political Content</h2>

    <p>
        Political discussions are allowed.
    </p>

    <p>
        However, content whose primary purpose is recruiting, organizing,
        or aggressively promoting political movements, parties,
        or ideologies may be removed.
    </p>

    <p>
        VidCore is a platform for discussion, not political campaigning.
    </p>

    <h2>Adult Content</h2>

    <p>
        Adult or age-restricted content must be properly marked when such
        functionality is available.
    </p>

    <p>
        Failure to correctly mark age-restricted content may result in content
        removal or account suspension.
    </p>

    <h2>Copyright</h2>

    <p>
        Users are responsible for respecting intellectual property rights.
    </p>

    <p>
        When using material created by others, users should provide appropriate
        attribution whenever possible.
    </p>

    <p>
        VidCore reserves the right to remove content that violates copyright laws
        or upon receiving a valid complaint from a rights holder.
    </p>

    <h2>User Responsibility</h2>

    <p>
        Users are fully responsible for the content they upload, publish,
        or distribute through VidCore.
    </p>

    <p>
        The platform does not automatically endorse user-generated content.
    </p>

    <h2>Platform Security</h2>

    <p>The following actions are strictly prohibited:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Attempting to exploit bugs</li>
        <li>Attempting to gain unauthorized access</li>
        <li>Attacking platform infrastructure</li>
        <li>Interfering with service operation</li>
        <li>Circumventing restrictions or moderation systems</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Accounts involved in such activities may be permanently suspended.
    </p>

    <h2>Moderation</h2>

    <p>Moderators may:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Remove content that violates these rules</li>
        <li>Restrict access to features</li>
        <li>Suspend accounts temporarily</li>
        <li>Permanently ban accounts for severe or repeated violations</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        Moderation decisions are made to protect the platform and its users.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to These Rules</h2>

    <p>
        These guidelines may be updated as VidCore evolves.
    </p>

    <p>
        Continued use of the platform constitutes acceptance of the current
        version of these rules.
    </p>

    <hr>

    <p>
        Thank you for helping keep VidCore creative, open, and respectful.
    </p>
</div>